  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">iCMM</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In recognition of the fact that a significant proportion of the households in the target locations, just like the rest of South Sudan live beyond the reach of health facilities, resulting in sick children being brought late to the facility or not at all, the integrated Community Case Management (iCCM) is designed to avail curative services at the community level. The project will focus on assessment, classification, and treatment of malaria, pneumonia and diarrhoea amongst children aged 2-59 months at the community level with referral of severe cases to the nearest health facility.</narrative>
  </description>
